surveyISS 1.0.0
  • Reference

    replicate srvy_iss function for spatially-explicit input sample size for western, central and eastern gulf subregions

    srvy_iss_goa_wc_e.Rd

    replicate srvy_iss function for spatially-explicit input sample size for western, central and eastern gulf subregions

    srvy_iss_goa_wc_e(
  iters = 1,
  lfreq_data,
  specimen_data,
  cpue_data,
  strata_data,
  r_t,
  yrs = NULL,
  boot_hauls = FALSE,
  boot_lengths = FALSE,
  boot_ages = FALSE,
  al_var = FALSE,
  age_err = FALSE,
  region = NULL,
  save_interm = FALSE,
  match_orig = FALSE,
  save
)

    Arguments

    iters

    number of iterations (500 recommended)

    lfreq_data

    input dataframe

    specimen_data

    input dataframe

    cpue_data

    input dataframe

    strata_data

    input dataframe

    r_t

    input dataframe

    yrs

    any year filter >= (default = NULL)

    boot_hauls

    resample hauls w/replacement (default = FALSE)

    boot_lengths

    resample lengths w/replacement (default = FALSE)

    boot_ages

    resample ages w/replacement (default = FALSE)

    al_var

    include age-length variability (default = FALSE)

    age_err

    include ageing error (default = FALSE)

    region

    region will create a folder and place results in said folder

    save_interm

    save the intermediate results: original comps, resampled comps (default = FALSE)

    match_orig

    match the computed values to gap output (default = FALSE)

    save

    name to save output
